Colombian Stock Movers: Coltejer, Mineros, Pacific Rubiales

-- B y   C a m i l a   R u s s o
-- 
2011-04-05T20:33:30Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-05/colombian-stock-movers-coltejer-mineros-pacific-rubiales.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4 p.m. New York time.  The IGBC Index rose 1.7 percent to 14,607.69, while the
Colcap Index increased 0.8 percent to 1,722.18.  Coltejer SA (COLTEJ)  , the Medellin-based clothing maker
and exporter, dropped 2.3 percent to 85 centavos.  Colombia ’s
peso rose to a five-month high on speculation dollar inflows
will increase as the government brings in funds left abroad last
year, reducing revenue for exporters.  Mineros SA (MINEROS)  , Colombia’s largest gold-mining
company, jumped 3.9 percent to 6,440 pesos, the biggest increase
since Nov. 17. Gold futures surged to a record as sovereign-debt
concerns boosted demand for the precious metal as an alternative
asset.  Pacific Rubiales Energy Corp (PRE)  , the Toronto-based
 oil company  with fields in Colombia, climbed 5.5 percent to
53,800 pesos. Colombia plans to increase crude output to 1.15
million barrels a day by the end of 2014 from 785,000 barrels a
day last year, Mines and Energy Minister Carlos Rodado said
today in Cartagena.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Camila Russo in New York at 
 crusso15@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
